{"title": "TASK-27: KB Rule Enforcement Engine", "description": "The highest-frequency signal in the evolution queue (10+ unique evolutions, all variants of the same gap): CORE has no mechanism to detect or reject contradictory KB entries. add_knowledge and kb_update insert blindly -- if a new entry contradicts an existing one, both coexist silently. This degrades KB quality over time and causes CORE to receive conflicting guidance. Fix: add a contradiction-check hook in t_add_knowledge and t_kb_update that searches existing entries on same domain+topic before inserting, flags conflicts via Telegram, and rejects or merges duplicates automatically.", "subtasks": "{
  "27.A": {
    "title": "Audit current add_knowledge and kb_update for contradiction checks",
    "status": "pending",
    "items": [
      "27.A.1 Read t_add_knowledge and t_kb_update in core_tools.py via core_py_fn",
      "27.A.2 Confirm neither performs any search_kb check before insert",
      "27.A.3 Define contradiction detection logic: same domain+topic with conflicting instruction field",
      "27.A.GATE Audit complete, logic defined -> proceed to 27.B"
    ]
  },
  "27.B": {
    "title": "Add search_kb pre-check to t_add_knowledge",
    "status": "pending",
    "items": [
      "27.B.1 Before insert: call search_kb(domain=domain, query=topic) -- if match found, compare instruction fields",
      "27.B.2 If contradiction detected: return {ok: false, conflict: existing_entry, action: rejected} + notify_owner via Telegram",
      "27.B.3 If near-duplicate (same topic, same instruction): skip insert silently, return {ok: true, action: skipped_duplicate}",
      "27.B.V1 core_py_validate passes",
      "27.B.V2 debug_fn t_add_knowledge dry_run=true -- contradiction path fires correctly",
      "27.B.V3 patch_file -> build_status green",
      "27.B.GATE Contradiction check live -> proceed to 27.C"
    ]
  },
  "27.C": {
    "title": "Apply same check to t_kb_update + wire Telegram alert",
    "status": "pending",
    "items": [
      "27.C.1 Apply same pre-check logic to t_kb_update",
      "27.C.2 Telegram alert format: [KB CONFLICT] domain/topic -- existing vs proposed instruction",
      "27.C.3 Add conflict_count field to session_end hot reflection payload",
      "27.C.V1 core_py_validate passes",
      "27.C.V2 patch_file -> build_status green",
      "27.C.V3 test: insert conflicting KB entry -> verify Telegram alert fires",
      "27.C.GATE Both tools protected -> proceed to task_gate"
    ]
  },
  "task_gate": {
    "items": [
      "TGATE.1 All subtasks 27.A-27.C done",
      "TGATE.2 E2E: insert two contradicting KB entries -> second is rejected, Telegram alert received",
      "TGATE.3 railway_logs_live -- no errors",
